⇒  npx create-next-app@latest

⇒  npx create-next-app
    command to create app next.js

⇒  npx create-react-app {name} --template redux-typescript
    command to create react app using redux with typscript

⇒ npm install @mui/x-data-grid
    command to install material ui data grid

⇒ npm install @mui/material @emotion/react @emotion/styled
    command to install material ui

⇒ npm init @eslint/config@latest
    command to install eslint (when it is not installed on project creation)
    add this entry "eslint ./src/**/*.{ts,tsx};" in package.json scripts area

⇒ npm install eslint-plugin-json eslint-plugin-json-format --save-dev
    command to install eslint json plugin,

⇒ ⇒ npm run lint
    command to run lint

⇒ npm run lint -- --fix
    command to run lint with fix

⇒ npm install --save-dev husky
    command to install husky

⇒ npm install @commitlint/cli --save-dev
⇒ npm install @commitlint/config-conventional --save-dev
    command to install commitlint, it is not required for husky, only if you want to use commitlint convention

⇒ npx husky init
    command to initializer husky, it will create .husky folder

⇒ echo "npm test" > .husky/pre-commit
    command to add pre-commit hook
